context: <a4_0>The Duchy of Lancaster<a4_0/> is <a1_0>one of two royal duchies in England<a1_0/>. It has landholdings throughout the region and elsewhere, operating as <a2_0>a property company<a2_0/>, but also exercising the right of the Crown in the County Palatine of Lancaster. While the administrative boundaries changed in the <a0_0><b5_0><b7_0>1970s<b7_0/><b5_0/><a0_0/>, the county palatine boundaries remain the same as the historic boundaries. As a result, the <a3_0>High Sheriffs<a3_0/> for Lancashire, <b8_0>Greater Manchester<b8_0/> and <b6_0>Merseyside<b6_0/> are appointed "within the Duchy and County Palatine of Lancaster".
